<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The K tile is worth 5 points — making it one of Scrabble's premium consonants. When paired with N in the KN digraph, you get words where the K is silent in speech but loudly valuable on the board. KNIFE, KNIGHT, and KNACK all carry serious scoring potential from that 5-point K alone.</p>

